<td data-local-id=3D"d1b44c25-300a-4c30-9f83-30ab5c2bca99" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3d2a5b7435d4">Date &amp; Time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c8ca1622-16b5-42b9-a4ee-3c65dbf64345" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"71f6147b62bd">The date and time when the reservation ended (=
guest checked out), in UTC. Empty at the time of check-in.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b5c9d72f-0146-49b4-aaf7-2c87aad33f37">
<td data-local-id=3D"d3466948-9f47-4db4-8e85-cedbffac866c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ef6ea5e36850"><strong>Created (UTC)</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2b984186-e5a5-4185-b34a-8be14e09d734" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"779e163e22da">Date &amp; Time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"248c7af8-3b6e-440b-877a-ac62831e526b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b78c556018b6">The date and time when the reservation record =
was created in the system, in UTC.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"53eb314b-3d74-4a3c-a913-612f671dc3be">
<td data-local-id=3D"e2312f77-f970-49bf-a982-9d1371645aad" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"841238f1bdc9"><strong>Updated (UTC)</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2d1b7311-6439-4167-b060-86fe2e91c764" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"82ae21cba972">Date &amp; Time</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ecfb5d9b-c57f-4681-a87e-539a71c77b21" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6fddde43926c">The date and time when the reservation was las=
t updated, in UTC.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"5e80bc2887f3"><strong>Note:</strong> All date and time value=
s are provided in UTC using ISO 8601 format (e.g., <code>2026-04-28T14:00:0=
0Z</code>). If your property operates in a different time zone, you may nee=
d to convert these values in subsequent workflow steps.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"56b9d1e6-1006-448a-9572-c1fd19bd6943">
<h2 local-id=3D"9115839575a9" id=3D"ReservationCheckedIn-HowItWorks">How It=
 Works</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"c26bf093-901a-42b4-8e8e-2345513c1d0c">
<li local-id=3D"769fc903-9aed-4ee2-a75c-1d870b7e408e">
<p local-id=3D"3cd52815a127">When the workflow is activated, the <strong>Re=
servation Checked In</strong> trigger registers itself to listen for check-=
in events in your property.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a3c9f3d7-f743-483e-8468-2a2eb1e3cb6a">
<p local-id=3D"ab4fedfafc57">Whenever a reservation is checked in at your p=
roperty =E2=80=94 whether through the Mews Commander or any other integrate=
d system =E2=80=94 the system detects the change and sends an event notific=
ation to the trigger.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d8c9825d-1328-4905-8b94-5464c4d62971">
<p local-id=3D"d92d7a29e045">The trigger receives and validates the event t=
o ensure it is authentic and has not already been processed (duplicate even=
ts are automatically suppressed).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9a261e07-888b-483f-a10a-ea61d5c902c1">
<p local-id=3D"51e0ab8fd1e6">The reservation and guest details are extracte=
d and sent to the <strong>out</strong> output port, making them available t=
o the next steps in your workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eaf7b720-0428-44b9-bf27-a3fbfac2dff5">
<p local-id=3D"c53c2205a57b">When the workflow is deactivated, the trigger =
automatically stops listening for events.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"8eaa6b4bf2a8"><strong>Note:</strong> The trigger includes bu=
ilt-in duplicate event suppression. If the same check-in event is received =
more than once (e.g., due to a retry), it will only be processed once, prev=
enting duplicate workflow executions.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"ce9cf5b6-b468-43f9-a39a-17669de1ff10">
<h2 local-id=3D"34e54076f738" id=3D"ReservationCheckedIn-ExampleUseCases">E=
xample Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"a23da617-d85f-4e8d-90b4-fc0dcedd21a8">
<li local-id=3D"fb496b67-75a4-438c-a029-096a46983c63">
<p local-id=3D"c9235917ac49"><strong>Welcome message</strong> =E2=80=94 Whe=
n a guest checks in, automatically send a personalized welcome message via =
email or SMS with check-in details and useful property information.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"b03c4479-1fbf-4ffd-806d-6df89eace337">
<p local-id=3D"3f500a229a12"><strong>Room service notification</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Notify housekeeping or front desk staff when a guest has checked in =
so they can deliver welcome amenities or finalize room preparations.</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"558d7352-065d-4d5e-87e6-cf76b544213f">
<p local-id=3D"fc8879bb0e5f"><strong>VIP handling</strong> =E2=80=94 Check =
the <strong>Guest Loyalty Code</strong> or <strong>Business Segment ID</str=
ong> to identify VIP guests at check-in and trigger special workflows, such=
 as sending a complimentary drink voucher or notifying the general manager.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"68b2cf11-0cae-4ba4-b10d-ef8b106f0314">
<p local-id=3D"353bcae9d2c5"><strong>Upsell opportunities</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Use the <strong>Departure (UTC)</strong> field to calculate the length =
of stay and offer relevant upsell packages (e.g., spa treatments for longer=
 stays).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a4363d3c-925d-47db-ad27-77906dc472b7">
<p local-id=3D"7bca69ed6da4"><strong>External system synchronization</stron=
g> =E2=80=94 Push check-in data to third-party systems (e.g., a CRM, loyalt=
y platform, or guest experience app) so they reflect the guest's current st=
atus in real time.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"c29a403b-ad54-4282-a27f-650a73dbf49b">
<h2 local-id=3D"9d40458af7bc" id=3D"ReservationCheckedIn-ImportantNotes">Im=
portant Notes</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"98ca2ffe-e639-43b5-9f44-590=
49b3ef264" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"34631d46-c8d8-4f07-8c88-fb8179a4d1a1">
<th data-local-id=3D"e814c904-167b-4d38-ab84-e3cfbe7faead" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c57e4fafdeff">Topic</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"ce094e4b-6081-490f-a0fe-c312f6b473ed" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"155f9b44c1ba">Details</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cccab9c0-b4e9-4b40-9473-7ce7c433054f">
<td data-local-id=3D"1c19e170-9f8e-4f5e-82b7-b2f41fd4c158" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"172aa62b178f"><strong>One event per check-in</strong></p></t=
d>
<td data-local-id=3D"163d03be-2846-4f24-b709-be7d20f1eedf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78c7f4a30d5d">This trigger fires once when a reservation is =
checked in. Subsequent changes to the reservation (e.g., room moves, date e=
xtensions) will not fire this trigger again. Use dedicated triggers for tho=
se events if needed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"42b529b4-8f31-4744-9db4-8b152996bf0d">
<td data-local-id=3D"7f2a72ce-d3a5-43d8-8b27-a6835daba1f7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"984d26099dd1"><strong>Started (UTC) is always populated</str=
ong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3eefd4b5-a946-4130-a267-35afcff03a48" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9e3f5b9d7e20">Because this trigger fires specifically on the=
 check-in event, the <strong>Started (UTC)</strong> field will always conta=
in a value representing the exact moment the guest was checked in.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"71a04afc-af40-4674-b44d-0f0e34a5b6f1">
<td data-local-id=3D"0b3dc659-16c0-45c3-93c7-5c42523da0de" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6b7c70ebec9b"><strong>Guest fields may be empty</strong></p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0abe0ceb-cbe9-41b4-952f-ee64b2965273" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"86007d2f6072">Some guest fields (email, telephone, nationali=
ty, etc.) depend on the information available at the time of check-in. If a=
 field has not been filled in, it will be empty. Consider adding conditiona=
l logic in your workflow to handle missing values.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"993379b4-7fac-4f05-aca1-5ca9145b56db">
<td data-local-id=3D"c4eb549a-df4f-4e79-8485-44f007e6c934" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"92fe6639166f"><strong>All times are in UTC</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b7a82917-4ab0-4607-be27-75ce73f3bf4b" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b934f4766ea1">All date and time fields use UTC. If your work=
flow needs local time, add a conversion step after the trigger.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
